I believe you mean "you're", you know, the compound of you and are.  Not "your", which is possessive.  Furthermore... it's upon, not apon.  It's African, not afircan.  Countries, not countires.  Rather THAN, not then, a future tense.  And "would have been", not "would of been".  Stop trying to sound things out.  Didn't you maybe notice the wavy red line underneath all of your misspellings?  If you can't respect a language enough to use it properly, then don't fucking use it, ignorant peasant.
